iamese palace women, and how Siam responded to the intense imperialist pressures it faced in the late nineteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aEthnicityzThailandxHistoryy19th century. 0aEthnicityzThailandxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolygynyzThailandxHistoryy19th century. 0aPolygynyzThailandxHistoryy20th century. 0aSex rolexPolitical aspectszThailandxHistoryy19th century. 0aSex rolexPolitical aspectszThailandxHistoryy20th century. 4aAsian Studies. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aWomens Studies. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh  aThai royal concubines, Siam royal consorts, women in Thai history, Lanna history, Thai crypto-colonialism, King Chulalongkorn's reign.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501755521zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501755521zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501755521/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA